public interface KeyVal<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.io.Serializable

This interface allows the map-reduce framework to store data into files as key-value pairs. All aspects of the implementing class must be serializable. The generic types must match the generic types in the client's map and reduce classes.
